# Authors

Prometheus is built by Stefan Carter and a community of contributors.

## Primary Author

- **Stefan Carter** ([@StefanIsMe](https://github.com/StefanIsMe)) — design, lead development, release engineering. `<stefan@withapurpose.co>`

Stefan Carter is the copyright holder of the Prometheus codebase distributed
under the terms of the [MIT License](LICENSE). The full limitation of
liability and warranty disclaimer is set out in [DISCLAIMER.md](DISCLAIMER.md).

## Project Lineage

Prometheus is a hard fork of **[Strix](https://github.com/usestrix/strix)**
(© Strix contributors, Apache-2.0), extended with the engagement-folder
model, scope guardrail, 7-Question Gate, Always-Rejected /
Conditionally-Valid matrices, and 7 hunt playbooks ported from
**[Claude-BugHunter](https://github.com/elementalsouls/Claude-BugHunter)**
by Sachin Sharma (ElementalSouls, MIT), and the 9-stage pipeline shape,
N-run LLM voting, threat-model stage, SARIF 2.1.0 emission, and
`run_manifest.json` schema derived from
**[Visa Vulnerability Agentic Harness (VVAH)](https://github.com/visa/visa-vulnerability-agentic-harness)**
(© 2026 Visa, Inc., Apache-2.0).

Per-file attribution is preserved in the module docstrings under
`prometheus/` and in the playbook headers under `prometheus/playbooks/`.
See [INTEGRATION_PLAN.md](INTEGRATION_PLAN.md) for the full lineage plan.

## Upstream Authors and Copyright Holders

### Strix — © Strix contributors
- Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
- Source: <https://github.com/usestrix/strix>
- Contribution: full original codebase that Prometheus was forked and
  renamed from; agent runtime, CLI/TUI, sandbox lifecycle, multi-agent
  orchestration, proxy/browser/terminal/Python tools, knowledge store.

### Claude-BugHunter — © Sachin Sharma (ElementalSouls)
- Licensed under the MIT License
- Source: <https://github.com/elementalsouls/Claude-BugHunter>
- Contribution: engagement-folder scaffold (`prometheus/engagement/`),
  scope guardrail (`prometheus/engagement/scope.py`), 7-Question Gate
  (`prometheus/core/seven_question_gate.py`), Always-Rejected matrix
  (`prometheus/core/always_rejected.py`), Conditionally-Valid matrix
  (`prometheus/core/conditionally_valid.py`), recon framework
  (`prometheus/core/recon.py`), evidence-hygiene skill
  (`prometheus/skills/evidence_hygiene.py`), and the seven hunt playbooks
  under `prometheus/playbooks/`.

### Visa Vulnerability Agentic Harness (VVAH) — © 2026 Visa, Inc.
- Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
- Source: <https://github.com/visa/visa-vulnerability-agentic-harness>
- Contribution: 9-stage pipeline shape (Discovery & Modeling → Deep Dive &
  Verification → Synthesis, Chaining & Reporting), N-run deterministic
  LLM voting (`prometheus/core/n_run_voting.py`), per-stage model
  routing, `run_manifest.json` schema
  (`prometheus/core/run_manifest.py`), and SARIF 2.1.0 emission
  (`prometheus/report/`).

## Third-Party Acknowledgments

The Prometheus project additionally acknowledges the following
upstream projects and their maintainers, whose work is consumed at
runtime or build time:

- **[LiteLLM](https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm)** — unified LLM
  provider routing.
- **[Caido](https://github.com/caido/caido)** — HTTP proxy SDK used for
  request capture and replay.
- **[Nuclei](https://github.com/projectdiscovery/nuclei)** — referenced
  template format for reconnaissance.
- **[Playwright](https://github.com/microsoft/playwright)** — headless
  browser automation.
- **[Textual](https://github.com/Textualize/textual)** — terminal UI
  framework powering the interactive TUI.
- **[VulnBot](https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.13411)** — the Penetration
  Task Graph (PTG) planner is *inspired by* VulnBot's phase-based
  pentest workflow.
- **[shuvonsec/claude-bug-bounty](https://github.com/shuvonsec/claude-bug-bounty)** —
  vendored as part of the Claude-BugHunter skill bundle.

## Contributing

See [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md) for how to submit changes, and
[CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) for community standards. New
contributors are added to this file in their first merged pull request.

A full list of code contributors is generated automatically by GitHub
and is available under **Insights → Contributors** in the repository
UI.
